{"id":"gallows","term":"Gallows","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Heb. ‘ets, meaning “a tree” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Esther 6:4\">Esther 6:4</a>), a post or gibbet. In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 40:19\">Gen. 40:19</a> and <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 21:22\">Deut. 21:22</a> the word is rendered “tree.”</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Esther 6:4","Genesis 40:19","Deuteronomy 21:22"]}